/#
   A type defining to whom and where notice of execution should be given. The partyReference refers to one of the principal parties of the trade. If present the exerciseNoticePartyReference refers to a party, other than the principal party, to whome notice should be given.
 #/
record FpML5.reporting.ExerciseNotice {
  # The party referenced has allocated the trade identifier.
  partyReference : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

  # The party referenced is the party to which notice of exercise should be given by the buyer.
  exerciseNoticePartyReference : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

  businessCenter : string?

}

partyReference.Doc: The party referenced has allocated the trade identifier.
partyReference.Name: partyReference

exerciseNoticePartyReference.Doc: The party referenced is the party to which notice of exercise should be given by the buyer.
exerciseNoticePartyReference.Name: exerciseNoticePartyReference
